.TH "drm_mode_create_tv_margin_properties" 9 "drm_mode_create_tv_margin_properties" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_create_tv_margin_properties \- create TV connector margin properties
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_mode_create_tv_margin_properties
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called by a driver's HDMI connector initialization routine, this function
creates the TV margin properties for a given device. No need to call this
function for an SDTV connector, it's already called from
\fBdrm_mode_create_tv_properties\fP.
